  "prompt": "Update the sketch only. Replace the current sketch with this corrected version that removes pass-by-reference and uses a global lastBtnState variable properly. The full corrected sketch is:\n\n```\n// ============================================================\n//  Servo + LEDs Power-Aware Demo\n//  Arduino Uno — Beginner Friendly\n// ============================================================\n//  WIRING SUMMARY:\n//   Servo      -> Signal: D9 | VCC: External 5V | GND: Common GND\n//   LED Red    -> D5 -> 220 ohm -> GND   (zone: 0-60 deg)\n//   LED Yellow -> D6 -> 220 ohm -> GND   (zone: 61-120 deg)\n//   LED Green  -> D7 -> 220 ohm -> GND   (zone: 121-180 deg)\n//   Button     -> D2 -> GND  (INPUT_PULLUP, pause/resume)\n//\n//  SAFETY NOTES:\n//   Servo powered by EXTERNAL 5V supply (NOT Arduino 5V pin)\n//   External GND and Arduino GND share a common ground wire.\n//   Each LED uses a 220 ohm resistor -> ~14 mA per LED (safe).\n//   Button uses INPUT_PULLUP, no external resistor needed.\n// ============================================================\n\n#include <Servo.h>\n\nconst int SERVO_PIN  = 9;\nconst int LED_LEFT   = 5;\nconst int LED_CENTER = 6;\nconst int LED_RIGHT  = 7;\nconst int BTN_PIN    = 2;\n\nServo myServo;\n\nint  currentAngle = 0;\nint  sweepStep    = 2;\nbool paused       = false;\n\nbool     lastBtnState  = HIGH;\nunsigned long lastDebounce = 0;\nconst unsigned long DEBOUNCE_DELAY = 50;\n\nunsigned long lastMoveTime = 0;\nconst unsigned long MOVE_INTERVAL = 20;\n\nvoid allLedsOff() {\n  digitalWrite(LED_LEFT,   LOW);\n  digitalWrite(LED_CENTER, LOW);\n  digitalWrite(LED_RIGHT,  LOW);\n}\n\nvoid updateLeds() {\n  allLedsOff();\n  if (currentAngle <= 60) {\n    digitalWrite(LED_LEFT,   HIGH);\n  } else if (currentAngle <= 120) {\n    digitalWrite(LED_CENTER, HIGH);\n  } else {\n    digitalWrite(LED_RIGHT,  HIGH);\n  }\n}\n\nvoid moveSweep() {\n  if (millis() - lastMoveTime < MOVE_INTERVAL) return;\n  lastMoveTime = millis();\n  currentAngle += sweepStep;\n  if (currentAngle >= 180) {\n    currentAngle = 180;\n    sweepStep = -2;\n  } else if (currentAngle <= 0) {\n    currentAngle = 0;\n    sweepStep = 2;\n  }\n  myServo.write(currentAngle);\n}\n\nvoid handleButton() {\n  bool reading = digitalRead(BTN_PIN);\n  if (reading != lastBtnState) {\n    lastDebounce = millis();\n  }\n  if ((millis() - lastDebounce) > DEBOUNCE_DELAY) {\n    if (reading == LOW && lastBtnState == HIGH) {\n      paused = !paused;\n      Serial.print(\">> Servo \");\n      Serial.println(paused ? \"PAUSED\" : \"RESUMED\");\n    }\n  }\n  lastBtnState = reading;\n}\n\nvoid setup() {\n  Serial.begin(9600);\n  Serial.println(\"=== Servo + LEDs Power-Aware Demo ===\");\n  Serial.println(\"Press button on D2 to pause or resume.\");\n  myServo.attach(SERVO_PIN);\n  myServo.write(currentAngle);\n  pinMode(LED_LEFT,   OUTPUT);\n  pinMode(LED_CENTER, OUTPUT);\n  pinMode(LED_RIGHT,  OUTPUT);\n  pinMode(BTN_PIN, INPUT_PULLUP);\n  allLedsOff();\n  delay(500);\n}\n\nvoid loop() {\n  handleButton();\n  if (!paused) {\n    moveSweep();\n  }\n  updateLeds();\n}\n```",
